Big Picture
• Defect nucleation plays an important role in defect-free material volumes or if system 
size is reduced to the submicron level
• The stress required to nucleate a dislocation homogeneously sets an upper bound for the 
effectiveness of our strengthening mechanisms
• Understanding defect nucleation is part of the puzzle for understanding the breakdown 
of Hall-Petch scaling in nanocrystalline materials
